comments: Olynyk (UTA) slides his hand across Batum's (LAC) front and marginal contact occurs as Olynyk immediately removes his hand.
Dunn (UTA) legally contests Leonard's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) is jumping to Dunn's (UTA) side as marginal contact occurs during the shot near the rim.
Westbrook (LAC) establishes himself in Dunn's (UTA) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Batum (LAC) brings his hands towards Collins (UTA) and marginal contact occurs as the defensive switch occurs.
Olynyk (UTA) brings his hand towards George's (LAC) front and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Clarkson (UTA) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Powell (LAC) is moving alongside Clarkson's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Leonard (LAC) is moving alongside Dunn's (UTA) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.

As Collins (UTA) attempts to secure the rebound, his forearm makes some contact with Westbrook's (LAC) head as Westbrook secures the ball.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Powell (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball as he defends Clarkson's (UTA) drive.
Westbrook (LAC) cleanly blocks Clarkson's (LAC) driving shot attempt.
George (LAC) pursues the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Collins (UTA) as he secures the rebound.
George (LAC) is turning away from Markkanen's (UTA) body and marginal contact occurs as he defends the shot near the rim.
Powell (LAC) contests Markkanen's (UTA) shot near the rim and marginal contact occurs after the release.
George (LAC) legally contests Markkanen's (UTA) layup attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
George (LAC) contests Markkanen's (UTA) shot near the rim and marginal contact occurs after the release.
Leonard (LAC) is firming up over his left foot and absorbs the contact from Dunn (UTA) during the screen.
Markkanen (UTA) steps slightly forward towards George's (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Dunn (UTA) moves forward into George's (LAC) body and initiates contact that affects his jump shot attempt.
Markkanen (UTA) establishes himself in Leonard's (LAC) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
George (LAC) briefly places two hands on Olynyk (UTA) and immediately removes his hands as Olynyk rolls towards the basket.
Batum (LAC) and Olynyk (UTA) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
George (LAC) moves forward into Clarkson's (UTA) space and initiates body to body contact with Clarkson that affects his follow-through.
Clarkson (UTA) places his hand momentarily on Covington's (LAC) side and immediately removes his hand as the pick is set.
Clarkson (UTA) is moving alongside Leonard's (LAC) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Olynyk (UTA) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
As Leonard (LAC) attempts to receive the pass, he bobbles the ball and immediately gains possession.
Clarkson (UTA) legally contests Leonard's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Olynyk (UTA) legally contests Westbrook's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
